    <text type="letter">
        <body> 

            <pb xml:id="leaf001r" facs="loc.02199.001.jpg" type="recto"/>
            <opener>
                <dateline>
                    <name type="place">1708 Chestnut Street<lb/>Phila. Pa. U.S.A.<ptr target="loc.02199_n2"/></name>
                    <date when="1888-12-01">Saturday morning,</date>
                    <date when="1888-12-01">1st December <hi rend="italic">1888</hi></date>
                </dateline>
                <salute>My dear Walt,</salute>
            </opener>

            <p>I want to introduce to you my friend Edward Pease<ptr target="n4978"/> of London (or
                more properly Newcastle)&#8212;he will be able to tell you about your numerous
                friends in Newcastle &#38; London.</p>

            <p>When my dear mother<ptr target="n0259"/> was initiating "The Free Will Offering"<ptr
                target="loc.02199_n1"/> in London Edward Pease was the first to render advice &#38;
                practical assistance, all of <choice><abbr>wch</abbr><expan>which</expan></choice> he did in a very charming way. Our friend is of
                well known Quaker stocke.&#8212; He is going stay some little time in Philadelphia. I
                hope to come over &#38; see you soon&#8212;</p>  

            <closer>
                <salute>With all love&#8212;</salute>
                <signed>Herbert Gilchrist</signed>
            </closer>
